-# Megabonk Reroll (BonkScanner)
+# BonkScanner
+
+BonkScanner is a Windows desktop tool for Megabonk map rerolling. It reads map stats directly from the game process, evaluates each run in real time, and restarts the run until a target map is found.
+
+The project has moved beyond the old console-first workflow: the main user experience is now a `customtkinter` GUI with template management, a configurable score system, session stats, native hook restart support, and in-app update checks.
+
+## What It Does
+
+- Reads map data directly from process memory instead of OCR.
+- Supports two evaluation modes:
+  - `Templates`: match maps against explicit minimum stat requirements.
+  - `Scores`: rank maps using weighted values and quality tiers.
+- Restarts runs automatically with either:
+  - standard keyboard input; or
+  - the native hook restart path.
+- Waits for stable ready-state snapshots before evaluating a map.
+- Pauses when the game window is not active, then resumes automatically.
+- Tracks per-session reroll statistics in the GUI.
+- Can check GitHub releases and update the packaged `.exe`.
+
+## Main Features
+
+### GUI-first workflow
+
+The app launches into a desktop UI implemented in [gui.py](/F:/Python/MegabonkReroll/gui.py). From there you can:
+
+- select active built-in templates;
+- create, edit, and delete custom templates;
+- switch between `Templates` and `Scores` tabs;
+- change hotkeys and timing settings;
+- enable or disable native hook restart;
+- inspect logs and current session stats without editing files manually.
+
+### Templates mode
+
+Template mode compares live map stats against profiles stored in `config.json`. Built-in templates include:
+
+- `LIGHT`
+- `MERCHANT`
+- `GOOD`
+- `PERFECT`
+- `PERFECT+`
+- `BOSS RUSH`
+- `BOSS RUSH+`
+
+Custom templates can also require minimum counts for:
+
+- combined `S+M`;
+- `Shady Guy`;
+- `Moais`;
+- `Microwaves`;
+- `Boss Curses`.
+
+### Scores mode
+
+Scores mode evaluates a map with weighted values from [logic.py](/F:/Python/MegabonkReroll/logic.py) and [config.py](/F:/Python/MegabonkReroll/config.py).
+
+Current score inputs include:
+
+- `Moais`
+- `Shady Guy`
+- `Boss Curses`
+- `Magnet Shrines`
+- a microwave multiplier
+
+The GUI exposes tier thresholds and weight tuning for:
+
+- `Light`
+- `Good`
+- `Perfect`
+- `Perfect+`
+
+Thresholds can be auto-scaled from the configured weights or edited manually.
+
+### Stable memory readiness
+
+Before a run is evaluated, the scanner waits for map generation to settle and requires two matching ready-state snapshots. That reduces dirty reads and makes reroll decisions more reliable.
 
